  <h2>ADA Service Dog Definition</h2>
  <div class="definition-box">
    <p><strong>Under the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), a service animal is:</strong></p>
    <blockquote>
      "A dog that has been <strong>individually trained</strong> to do work or perform tasks for an individual with a disability. The task(s) performed by the dog must be <strong>directly related</strong> to the person's disability."
    </blockquote>
  </div>

